bib_record.title: High precision measurements of the pion-proton elastic differential cross sections in the second resonance region.

free_txt: Two chambers closest to the target have a
sensitive area of 600*400 mm2. Six other chambers have
sensitive area of 1200*800 mm2. A gas mixture of 70%
Ar and 30% CO2 is used in the drift chambers.
Selection of the elastic events is based on the angular
correlation of pion and proton tracks.
Beam pollution of electrons and muons
The secondary pion beam line of the ITEP proton
Liquid hydrogen placed into mylar reservoir (40 mm in
diameter and 250 mm length along the beam) was used as
Data were received from Dr. I.G.Alekseev.
